Sure! Below is a simple web game that teaches truth table logic through analogies with Dungeons & Dragons (D&D) spellcasting. The game is designed to be entirely in a single HTML file, with embedded CSS and JavaScript.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>D&D Spellcasting Logic Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #b30000;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            margin: 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
        .result {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 1.5em;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Spellcasting Logic Game</h1>
    <p>Cast "Fireball" or "Healing" using the following spell combination:</p>
    <p>
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="wizard" /> Wizard (A)</label><br />
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="cleric" /> Cleric (B)</label><br />
    </p>
    <button onclick="castSpell()">Cast Spell</button>

    <div class="result" id="result"></div>

    <script>
        function castSpell() {
            const wizard = document.getElementById('wizard').checked;
            const cleric = document.getElementById('cleric').checked;
            let result = 'Invalid Cast!';

            if (wizard && cleric) {
                result = 'You cast "Fireball" and receive "Healing"! (A AND B)';
            } else if (wizard) {
                result = 'You cast "Fireball"! (A)';
            } else if (cleric) {
                result = 'You receive "Healing"! (B)';
            } else {
                result = 'No spell cast! (NEITHER)';
            }

            document.getElementById('result').innerText = result;
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Run the Game:
1. Copy the entire code above.
2. Paste it into a text editor and save the file with the `.html` extension (e.g., `dd_logic_game.html`).
3. Open the file in a web browser.

### Game Explanation:
- The game presents the player with two characters from D&D: a Wizard (A) and a Cleric (B).
- The player can check the boxes to select which spells they'd like to "cast."
- Depending on the combination of checked characters, the game will explain what spell was cast according to the rules of logic:
  - If both are selected, the result represents the logical AND (A AND B).
  - If only one is selected, it represents the individual casts.
  - If neither is selected, it indicates no spell has been cast.

This way, players can learn about truth tables through a fun and engaging game!

Certainly! Below is an updated version of the D&D spellcasting logic game that includes ten levels, each with increasing logical complexity. The game uses combinations of AND, OR, and NOT operations, which are illustrated through spellcasting scenarios. 

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>D&D Spellcasting Logic Game</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f2f2f2;
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #b30000;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            margin: 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #45a049;
        }
        .result {
            margin-top: 20px;
            font-size: 1.5em;
        }
        .level {
            margin-top: 30px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Spellcasting Logic Game</h1>
    <div id="level-container" class="level"></div>
    <div>
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="a" /> Wizard (A)</label><br />
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="b" /> Cleric (B)</label><br />
        <label><input type="checkbox" id="c" /> Rogue (C)</label><br />
    </div>
    <button onclick="castSpell()">Cast Spell</button>

    <div class="result" id="result"></div>

    <script>
        const levels = [
            // Level 1
            {
                description: "Level 1: Use Wizard A or Cleric B.",
                logic: (a, b, c) => a ? "You cast 'Fireball'! (A)" : b ? "You cast 'Healing'! (B)" : "No spell cast! (NEITHER)"
            },
            // Level 2
            {
                description: "Level 2: Use Wizard A and Cleric B.",
                logic: (a, b, c) => (a && b) ? "You cast 'Fireball' and receive 'Healing'! (A AND B)" : "No combined spell cast! (A AND B)"
            },
            // Level 3
            {
                description: "Level 3: Use Wizard A or (Cleric B AND Rogue C).",
                logic: (a, b, c) => a ? "You cast 'Fireball'! (A)" : (b && c) ? "You cast 'Healing' and 'Sneak Attack'! (B AND C)" : "No spell cast! (NEITHER)"
            },
            // Level 4
            {
                description: "Level 4: Use NOT Wizard A AND Cleric B.",
                logic: (a, b, c) => (!a && b) ? "You receive 'Healing', but no 'Fireball'! (NOT A AND B)" : "Invalid cast!"
            },
            // Level 5
            {
                description: "Level 5: Use (Wizard A AND NOT Cleric B).",
                logic: (a, b, c) => (a && !b) ? "You cast 'Fireball', but no 'Healing'! (A AND NOT B)" : "Invalid cast!"
            },
            // Level 6
            {
                description: "Level 6: Use Wizard A OR (Cleric B AND Rogue C).",
                logic: (a, b, c) => a ? "You cast 'Fireball'! (A)" : (b && c) ? "You cast 'Healing' and 'Sneak Attack'! (B AND C)" : "No spell cast! (NEITHER)"
            },
            // Level 7
            {
                description: "Level 7: Use (NOT Wizard A OR Cleric B).",
                logic: (a, b, c) => (!a || b) ? (!a ? "No 'Fireball' but you cast 'Healing'! (NOT A OR B)" : "You cast 'Fireball'! (A)") : "No spell cast!"
            },
            // Level 8
            {
                description: "Level 8: Use Wizard A AND (Cleric B OR Rogue C).",
                logic: (a, b, c) => (a && (b || c)) ? "You cast 'Fireball' with either 'Healing' or 'Sneak Attack'! (A AND (B OR C))" : "Invalid cast!"
            },
            // Level 9
            {
                description: "Level 9: Use (NOT Wizard A AND NOT Cleric B) OR Rogue C.",
                logic: (a, b, c) => (!a && !b) || c ? (c ? "You cast 'Sneak Attack'! (C)" : "No spell cast") : "Invalid cast!"
            },
            // Level 10
            {
                description: "Level 10: Use (Wizard A AND Rogue C) OR NOT Cleric B.",
                logic: (a, b, c) => (a && c) || !b ? (a && c ? "You cast 'Fireball' and 'Sneak Attack'! (A AND C)" : "No 'Healing' but you can do something else! (NOT B)") : "Invalid cast!"
            },
        ];

        let currentLevel = 0;

        function loadLevel() {
            const levelContainer = document.getElementById('level-container');
            levelContainer.innerHTML = `<h2>${levels[currentLevel].description}</h2>`;
        }

        function castSpell() {
            const a = document.getElementById('a').checked;
            const b = document.getElementById('b').checked;
            const c = document.getElementById('c').checked;

            const result = levels[currentLevel].logic(a, b, c);
            document.getElementById('result').innerText = result;

            // Move to the next level if the spell was valid
            if (result.includes('cast')) {
                currentLevel++;
                if (currentLevel < levels.length) {
                    loadLevel();
                } else {
                    document.getElementById('result').innerText += "\nYou completed all levels!";
                }
            }
        }

        // Initialize the game
        loadLevel();
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```

### How to Run the Game:
1. Copy the entire code above.
2. Paste it into a text editor and save the file with the `.html` extension (e.g., `dd_logic_game.html`).
3. Open the file in a web browser.

### Game Explanation:
- The game has ten levels with increasing complexity in logic.
- The player must check the appropriate boxes to cast spells according to the logic defined for each level.
- The game explains what spell was cast based on the logical expressions given for each level.
- The player progresses through the levels by casting spells correctly. If they fail to cast a valid spell, they will not advance to the next level. 

This structure helps players learn about logical operations while enjoying a Dungeons & Dragons-themed game experience!

